extendedInfo.description: GDocs Export Free (Ad Supported!) allows users to download their Google Documents to their Android device in many formats.  GDocs Export  allows you to download all types of Google Documents in the following formats:Word processing documents*Microsoft Word (.doc)*Adobe PDF (.pdf)*Rich Text Format (.rtf)*Text file (.txt)*OpenDocument Text (.odt)*HTML (.html)*ZIP - zipped up HTML (.zip)Spreadsheets*Microsoft Excel (.xls)*Adobe PDF (.pdf)*HTML (.html)*OpenDocument Spreadsheet (.ods)Presentations*Microsoft PowerPoint (.ppt)*Adobe PDF (.pdf)*Text file (.text)*PNG (.png)*Shockwave Flash (.swf)PDFs*Adobe PDF (.pdf)Drawings/Images*Portable Network Graphic (.png)*JPEG (.jpeg)*Adobe PDF (.pdf)*Scalable Vector Graphic (.svg)Other Files*Ability to download files that haven't been converted by Google DocsMany more formats and document types will be quickly added in subsequent releases.  Once you download your documents you can then open it (document viewing software required for this functionality) or share it via Gmail/email with family, friends, or colleagues.--Future Features--Upload documents from your Android deviceDownload multiple documents at onceConvert documents from one type to another--Privacy Statement--GDocs Export does NOT save or use your Google account credentials in anyway outside the scope and purpose of this application.--Support--If you have any issues, questions, or any features you would like regarding GDocs Export, please contact me.

reviews.title: Unusable with many documents
reviews.comment: No search, no tags, no directories, no fastscroll. A plus is that it can sort the docs list by name.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great tool!
reviews.comment: Allows me to export all of my Google document files so I can read them on my device and share them with coworkers.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: Would give 0 stars..document too small n was unable to zoom to view..mytouch 4g slide..UNINSTALLING. waste of time.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: File types not there
reviews.comment: The description promises that you can export in jpg format, but in the app, jpg doesn\'t appear in the list of choices for file type!
reviews.author: A Google User
